  "StockRole": "Sniper",
  "YangsThoughts": "The Federated Commonwealth rejected this one for being too slow and underarmored for its weight, which tells you something about how they think. The Taurian Concordat saw it differently, and honestly I side with them. Three Gauss Rifles on one frame is not something you just walk away from. Production line got wrecked in the Jihad and the design nearly vanished entirely. Finding one of these still operational is like finding a fossil that can still bite.",
